detailed_reviews.review_text: Honestly a gem in this area. Clean environment with AC. Reasonable prices. Milk tea was alright especially for $3! Wonton soup has a strong white pepper flavour. Would come back again!

Very nice, well decorated and ultra clean restaurant.  Great attention and very food food. Maybe a bit Americanized profile in flavor, but very good as it is. My wife and I couldnt eat any more and spent $48 including  the tip.
This place is very delicious. I have tried a few of their vegetarian dishes and all of them have been scrumptious, especially the tofu. I cant wait to try more

this place is a very good place to visit for a quick lunch. The food taste great and is affordable, and its so convenient especially if youre just wanting a quick bite. The staff is great and super attentive. I will keep coming back. Definitely a good spot, they have a really cute and simple patio as well. This spot is by commercial skytrain station.
Great BBQ pork over rice, try it with the extra Sunnyside egg,  very affordable and filling.
They serve very reasonable noodle. If you dont mind to spend time to look for a parking, highly recommend!

Got some dim sum via delivery on DoorDash as a sort of late Lunar New Year treat for me and my boo.  The delivery time expected was the fastest offered when I used dim sum as a search term-and they did NOT disappoint! For those of you who would like to read further, I shall elaborate.  The packaging was thoughtfully done with sturdy circular cardboard containers-not the kind I can keep as tupperware but eminently recyclable.  The sauces were kept in cute lil plastic containers inside the containers of their respective dishes-as a result of this thoughtful packaging, all foods and sauces arrived with only a few drops of spillage. We ordered a combination of hot dim sum and cold Hong Kong style iced tea as well as some frozen dumplings for later.  They were kept in appropriately separated paper bags, keeping the hot stuff hot (but not burningly so), and the cold stuff cold.  A solid A well deserved on the delivery front.  Now to taste. The frozen potstickers I ordered I sadly cannot include in this review as I have not eaten them. The Hong Kong style tea was very strong, but not very sweet.  I have a bit of a sweet tooth so I didn t love it myself but if you prefer watching your sugar intake I think you ll definitely like it. The dim sum selection wasn t huge but the items were excellent!  I had red bean sesame balls, black sesame buns, steamed shrimp dumplings, char siu (pork dumplings with a single wonton wrapping), deep fried pork buns, and popcorn chicken. I ll list them in order: Red Bean Sesame Balls: Fantastic.  I had them elsewhere and found them quite greasy.  Here they weren t, but still had their wonderful earthy character. Black Sesame Buns: My boo especially liked these due to their softness.  For me the black sesame filling was quite competently done.   Nuff said! Shrimp Dumplings: Exactly what you would expect in this town-nice, moist and warm.  Went with the mild soy sauce quite nicely. Char Siu: Wonderfully juicy.  The mild soy sauce that dripped on them slightly played off the pork brilliantly too. Deep Fried Pork Buns:  What is rich and salty for me is quite beloved by my boo, and these treats were no exception.  I let him have the majority. Popcorn Chicken:  The lone disappointment-though well seasoned, the popcorn bits were very often small enough in this dish that they could not contain chicken.  The pieces that did have chicken though were quite tasty and went quite well with a sweet ish sauce we mixed up ourselves. Overall, this delivery was extremely well done and I very much look forward to the day that I can visit this Hon s branch in person.

detailed_reviews.review_text: Location is great for public transit riders making a transfer at the Broadway Commercial station.  It was mid-afternoon when I entered and no one before me. It still took sometime to get one dish on the table. There are probably more staff during busier hours than one cook. Food quality was good and delicious. Price was below average and I think reasonable. Hons is well known for its quality food at good prices. Will definitely try it again when I transit at Broadway station again.
The restaurant is clean, and the service is good. The food flavour is ok but nothing special. They serve the dishes very fast.
I have been eating in Hon s since many years ago from downtown spot and today I eat in E Broadway. Good food, thin noodle, great caring, reasonable price, with alfresco area to eat.
